<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-01-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="465" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                    <head>No. 463.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-01-29"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 29,
                            1874</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 71.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch, No. 93, of the 14th instant,
                        relative to Mexican bonds held by citizens of the United States, has been
                        received.</p>
                    <p>The statement of those bonds promised to you by Mr. Mejia, the minister of
                        finance of Mexico, will be awaited with interest.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>